		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV><EM>Such a server as suggested here, would have an extremely small following. I don't see a lot of time-seasoned adventurers wanting to re-live the hours waiting for boats to travel a continent to get some violence on... or just to get to mainland Antonica for that matter (/shiver). </EM></DIV>
<DIV><EM></EM>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>First, those in Time are less than 1% of the player base, 97% will <STRONG>never</STRONG> get there.&nbsp; This thread has had over 100 replies, another on the same topic is approaching 50, how is that an extremely small following?&nbsp; A petition for a Classic style server was posted 2 nights ago (deleted the next morning), in a few early-morning hours it had over a dozen replies.&nbsp; Discord was one of the highest population servers when it was up, and half the people who tried it probably quit the first time they died.&nbsp; A huge player base is <EM>already here</EM>, <U>all but screaming</U> for a chance to sit on those boats for half an hour, begging for a smaller world&nbsp;where they can be stuck in top-notch gear that doesn't even max out their stats, all so they can PvP the way it used to be, <U><STRONG><FONT color=#ffff00 size=2>the way it should be</FONT></STRONG></U>.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>But,&nbsp;I already know why no one has listened to us, the only thing that goes through Sony's mind when they see this is "Lower expansion sales."&nbsp; Listen to what&nbsp;I am saying, the people who want this server will not be buying OoW either way, likely they will not go near the next one either.&nbsp; Continuing to turn a deaf ear to them will <EM>not</EM> gain you expansion sales, it will <EM>lose</EM> you subscriptions.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The Craft of War&nbsp;looms on the horizon, it will detour players from EQ2 and remove them from EQ1, both in the tens of thousands.&nbsp; <STRONG><U>Listen</U></STRONG> to those players and lessen the damage!</DIV>	
		</td></tr>
