			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=PVP&message.id=1361#M1361">110</a> of 128
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 463 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>Sam&nbsp;I&nbsp;don't understand, are you suggesting having specific zones for PvP and removing it from the rest?&nbsp; If so all servers have that already, they're called Arenas.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>
<P><EM>Verant already tried the new server trick. Introducing Sullon Zek, THE failed experiment heh. </EM></P>
<P>The failure of SZ was twofold&nbsp;I think, parts were flawed from the beginning but the players ruined the rest.&nbsp; I played on SZ when it was in beta on the test patcher, a High Elven Wizard, and&nbsp;I have to say it was some of the most enjoyable time&nbsp;I ever had in the game.&nbsp; It was exciting to see people adventuring in a world they knew, yet which was completely unpredictable to them.&nbsp; Players staying in character, shouting in GFay how their guild was the first to take down the mighty Orc Trainer, beaming with pride even though they hadn't gotten the SBS.&nbsp; I remember the many guilds that were folrmed on the basis of a Good-Neutral Alliance because we all saw the danger the Evil team posed with sole posession of Kunark (bet SZ wishes they had listened to us back then eh? hehe).&nbsp; It was nice to have a PvP environment where every person you saw wasn't automatically a threat, even some of the ones on different teams.&nbsp; However,&nbsp;I now see the flaws that were there from the start, from day 1 of live SZ the scum of the other servers swarmed over, they saw "no rules, attack any lvl" and were hooked.&nbsp; Having no rules in the interest of RP PvP is all well and good, if another team Steals your Kill get some friends and fight them for it, but you have to remember some rules (like training and corpse/bind/zone camping) are not there to hamper competition, but are in place to prevent exploitation of game mechanics, and should have been left on Sullon.&nbsp; I also think haveing no lvl restriction for PvP caused many problems,&nbsp;I like the idea of everyone being able to join in the fight but players chose to use their lvl advantage to just prevent others from lvling, just as Evil now prevents Good and Neutral from advancing beyond VT.</P>
<P>I realize there's already been plenty of discussion on ideas for the new server Ruleset, and we're now pretty much in the "get someone at Sony to actually read this" stage, but&nbsp;I can't help thinking about possibilities:</P>
<P></P>
<HR>

<P>Sullon Zek ruleset just as it was from the start (but with evil being able to attack evil)&nbsp;with only 2 alterations;</P>
<P>1.&nbsp;PvP enabled at lvl 1, item loot enabled for all characters past lvl 19.&nbsp; Both victim <EM>and</EM> victor must be lvl 20 or higher for an item to be looted, and once reaching lvl 20 you cannot dlvl back to 19.</P>
<P>2. Upon reaching lvl 20 your kills will be point-tallied by team of the victim, and if at any time the majority (3/4 or more)&nbsp;of your kills-to-date are contrary to your current team, you will be switched to a different team thusly:</P>
<BLOCKQUOTE dir=ltr>
<P>i. Good characters who primarily kill Neutrals will become Evil.</P>
<P>ii. Neutral characters who primarily kill Goods will become Evil and vice-versa.</P>
<P>iii. Evil characters&nbsp;who primarily kill Evils will become Neutral.</P></BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>It allows for everything SZ was meant to create while preventing most of the major shortfalls.&nbsp; I only include item loot because PvP can get very stangant without it in my opinion, and people need an incentive to lvl past 20 other than just the advantage over lower characters, it could be replaced with PvP point items, or perhaps Raid zones open only to the current leading team, rather easily.</P>
<P></P>
<HR>

<P><EM>Before they consider opening NEW servers, the players on the old ones need taken care of first. </EM></P>
<P>I agree, but it is impossible to make everyone on the current servers happy no matter how many/few changes are made, a Classic server would provide a better option for the Casual/Roleplayers, not to mention bringing back many players who have gone Blue or quit altogether, and therefore the changes to current Servers could be more tailored to the remaining characters.&nbsp; The Classic server will not be a place for&nbsp;power gamers and full time raiders, it will be a haven for people who like PvP for the actual PvP not just their gear advantage.&nbsp;</P>
<P><EM>And if they do create a new server, without the option to /movelog existing PvPrs there Id wager people will quit. Why? The time investment. Alot of people enjoy the current PvP servers, and would enjoy them moreso if decent improvements existed. </EM></P>
<P>The entire point of a Classic server is to have a place without Movelogged or twinked characters, everyone starts on the same field, you don't have to consign your life away to raiding just to get gear enough to survive, and even those who do raid will not have the gross, unfair advantage over the casual player that they do now.&nbsp; Your starting stats and PvP skill used to actually matter, now people run around with 20 items that each give more bonuses than an entire suit used to.&nbsp; And&nbsp;I certainly don't see how adding a new server would ever make anyone quit, <STRONG><U>lack</U></STRONG> of options is what makes people leave.</P>
<P><EM>Right now your preaching how a classic server would solve this and that. </EM></P>
<P>It will solve the problem for many of us, or we wouldn't ask for it.</P>
<P><EM>Eventually that server would corrode because of players going "what all this is is PvP **SMURF** wheres the content?" </EM></P>
<P>I don't even know how to begin to respond to that.&nbsp; The point of a PvP server is to have PvP!!!!!&nbsp; We have blue servers for content, you're welcome to them.</P>
<P><EM>Weve got 4 Zek servers. Fix those THEN worry bout suggesting a classic or pre-Luclin PvP server folks</EM></P>
<P>For the 5th time<EM>&nbsp;I agree</EM>, fix the current servers for those who wish to stay on them, but don't force the rest out onto the metaphorical street give&nbsp;them someplace to go too!&nbsp; I fully intend to continue on Rallos after the Classic server comes out (yes, considering we've only had one official response to this idea at all, and it was negative and wrongly assumed that people only stay in the game for expansions,&nbsp;I seem foolishly optimistic, but hey, a little optimism can't hurt) unless of course most of my friends/guildies moved as well, they are the main reason&nbsp;I stick around afterall.</P>
<P>*<EM>Knocks on the screen</EM>* "Anybody at Sony even read this yet?"</P></DIV>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
