<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=PVP&message.id=3132#M3132">114</a> of 128
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 389 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<BR>
<BLOCKQUOTE>
<P>
<HR>
</P>
<P>Trynd wrote:</P>
<P>Sony (Verant originally) correctly identified that there is a particular segment of the mmorpg player-base who is primarily motivated by PvP combat and the fun that arises from it and that these players value PvP combat above all other factors when determining their level of satisfaction with the game.&nbsp; PvPers, by definition, want PvP.&nbsp; </P>
<DIV>
<HR>
</DIV></BLOCKQUOTE><BR>
<DIV>Unfortunately, Trynd's entire argument is fundamentally flawed.&nbsp; He bases his assertions upon the assumption that&nbsp;all&nbsp;individuals&nbsp;on each of&nbsp;the PvP servers have identical reasons for&nbsp;playing there.&nbsp; While some may thrill at the simple act of killing another, others may not.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Everquest began as a roleplaying game.&nbsp; Whether it remains such (or whether Sony cares) is a matter of conjecture.&nbsp; However, many of us began playing on PvP servers to add more versatility to our roleplaying.&nbsp; For us, Everquest is not a first-person shooter; we enjoy the roleplay aspect and use PvP to that end.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>If you crave hardcore, first-person shooters, might I suggest playing Quake, Unreal, or any of the other numerous games geared towards such inane bloodlust...instead of making sweeping generalizations about what we, as a community, desire.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>~Anakah, The Insane~</DIV>
<DIV>65th Lord Protector of the Temple of Light</DIV>
<DIV>&lt;Rallos Zek&gt;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>"Insanity is doing the same thing over and over, expecting a different result."</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>"Courage of the heart is very rare; the stone has a power when it's there."&nbsp;-Nicodemus, Leader of the Rats of NIMH-</DIV>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
