		</td></tr>
		
	<tr>
	
		<td class="msg_user_cell" width="150" valign=top>
		
			 









<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=52769'  class="auth_text"  style="font-weight:bold;" >	
Anakah_RZ</a>
			<br>
			
			<span style="font-size: 8pt;">
			Newbie<br>
			
				Posts: 5<br>
				
				Registered: 07-15-2004
				
			</span>
			


			
			<br>
			
				<img src="/i/p.gif" height=8 width=150 border=0 alt=""><br>
				
			<a href='/eq/view_profile?user.id=52769'>







</a><br>
			


			
			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=PVP&message.id=3141#M3141">118</a> of 128
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 350 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>The point, Falstafe, is the focus.&nbsp; PvP is an aspect of roleplay, not the other way around.&nbsp;&nbsp;To&nbsp;reverse that, making PvP the sole reason to play on a given server...and "roleplay" simply&nbsp;a way one goes about it...?&nbsp; Well, it's just not what I call a ROLEPLAYING game.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Further, for the playerkillers, gankers, profiteers, griefers, and exploiters experiencing delusions that they are somehow oppressed by the greater populace, I say tough cookies.&nbsp; The world of Norrath is a reflection of the real world.&nbsp; Whether we roleplay or not, a threat to the wellbeing of our avatars in Norrath is going to be viewed in a negative light.&nbsp; If you kill another player, grief them, camp them, ruin their epic handin for your own delight...yes, you will be hunted, ostracized from our groups and guilds, and estranged from the populace at large.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Remember that a good roleplaying game, while fantasy, is anchored to some extent in the realities of our world.&nbsp; It is by this fact that we are able to imagine, roleplay, and, ultimately, become our avatars, during our brief stays in Norrath.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Accept the facts:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>If you kill me...no...I'm probably not going to like it.&nbsp; I don't want you in my group, my guild, or anywhere near me.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>If you kill my friends...no...I'm probably not going to like it.&nbsp; Again, I don't want you in my group, my guild, or anywhere near me.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>If you ninja-loot, randomly kill people, kill-steal the mob I've been camping for 15 hours straight, ETC...you get the picture?</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>This is not to say that we all have to play nice.&nbsp; If you wish to play an assassin, a bandit, or a serial killer, fine...but expect that other players will probably not want to associate with you, at the very least.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Roleplay your religion.&nbsp; Roleplay your race.&nbsp; Roleplay your class.&nbsp; Make up a history for your avatar.&nbsp; Decide why he/she feels and acts in certain ways.&nbsp; Develop a personality for your avatar.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Really, though, the argument about PvP in regards&nbsp;to these&nbsp;"PK's" is truly moot.&nbsp; I've read through their posts on these boards, many from Rallos Zek (where I play).&nbsp; I find it amusing that they talk about the "flawed" ruleset that oppresses them and forces them to be outcasts.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>So-called "Anti's" PvP all the time.&nbsp; We PvP in fun.&nbsp; We PvP in roleplay.&nbsp; But we do not PvP with the sole desire to disrupt another player's experience of the game.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>The "PK" posts that litter these boards are written by players with a very different view of PvP, to say the least.&nbsp; To these players, PvP is about <EM>winning</EM>.&nbsp; It's about causing another player grief, getting some sick satisfaction from the misery of others.&nbsp; (Find a hobby.)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>These are the players that...</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>...train 10 mobs onto you just to watch you and your group die.</DIV>
<DIV>...train your raid to watch you wipe.</DIV>
<DIV>...snare and DoT you while you're fighting a mob, so that you get an exp death.</DIV>
<DIV>...nuke you at 20% HP, while you have 2 mobs beating on you (and somehow believe it took skill).</DIV>
<DIV>...corpse camp you until you log.</DIV>
<DIV>...bind and zone camp, killing you before your screen even loads.</DIV>
<DIV>...kill your quest mob, after you've made the handin.</DIV>
<DIV>...use exploits to kill you.</DIV>
<DIV>...ninja-loot the mob that your raid just killed.</DIV>
<DIV>...spam you with obscenities and demeaning comments after it all.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>This isn't PvP; <STRONG>it's abusing your fellow players</STRONG>.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>In the end, the problem isn't the ruleset.&nbsp; The quality of play on any given server is predominantly governed by the quality of players that inhabit it.&nbsp; If anything, Sony's total disregard for the preservation of a roleplay environment is at fault.&nbsp; </DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>*The&nbsp;servers are grievously understaffed...to the point where <EM>customer service</EM> is a joke.&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>*Only the largest and most glaringly obvious policy violations are ever addressed.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>*A blindeye is turned to the abuse of other players by griefers and exploiters.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>If the environment is to improve, Sony needs to draw the line and say, <STRONG>"Hey..you folks are doing that just to disrupt the play of others.&nbsp; We don't need your twelve and change, because we respect the right of our other paying customers to enjoy the game."</STRONG></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Plenty of other games do it.&nbsp; It's sad that Sony allows the few to ruin the enjoyment of the masses.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>~Anakah, The Insane~</DIV>
<DIV>65th Lord Protector of the Temple of Light</DIV>
<DIV>&lt;Rallos Zek&gt;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>"Insanity is doing the same thing over and over, expecting a different result."</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>"Courage of the heart is very rare; the stone has a power when it's there."&nbsp;-Nicodemus, Leader of the Rats of NIMH-</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
