		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>I don't want to get into bantering back and forth with your inane little quips, Falstafe...but the heading of the thread distinctly says <STRONG>How to Fix EQ PvP - Address the real issue</STRONG>.&nbsp; Further, Trynd's original post includes some commentary on what should be done with existing live servers.&nbsp; As such, this is not a thread solely dedicated to the creation of a new PvP server.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>My post was in response to this, as well as the posts that followed from various members of the Rallos community who relish in the misery of others.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>My post did <STRONG>NOT </STRONG>state that everyone must roleplay.&nbsp; The idea is not to penalize those that don't roleplay; that's entirely up to them.&nbsp; However, the game shouldn't be tailored to the whims of a few <STRONG>special</STRONG> people that got lost in the store...and picked up Everquest, instead of Unreal Tournament.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>It's a roleplaying game.&nbsp; The focus, whether one decides to or not, is roleplaying.&nbsp; This focus should not shift to mindless killing for points, profit, or anything else.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>My advice...read a book, play a table-top RPG, and, if you must, play a couple rounds of your favorite shooter before signing into EQ...just to get it out of your system.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>~Anakah, The Insane~</DIV>
<DIV>65th Lord Protector of the Temple of Light</DIV>
<DIV>&lt;Rallos Zek&gt;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>"Insanity is doing the same thing over and over, expecting a different result."</DIV>
