		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			Possibly my last post to these forums (coincidentally, I made the first post to this forum when it was brought up... the future ruleset discussion thread).<br><br>"And if they do create a new server, without the option to /movelog existing PvPrs there Id wager people will quit."<br><br>True maybe, but one thing is certain. The lack of a PvP Classic Server is already causing one person to quit: me.<br><br>I've said elsewhere that I fully agree that the current PvP servers should be taken care of before any new rulesets are considered. But it's been announced that they are not considering any new rulesets at all. After the Discord experiment, it was announced that SOE would wait till after getting through the launch of GOD to consider bringing up any new experimental ruleset servers. I bought this account to play on Discord because it was a new idea. The perma death sucked... the classic-only ruled.<br><br>But just as SOE has changed its mind about PvP in EQII and tried to rewrite history by saying nothing was ever promised, now that PvP changes are being made there is no consideration by SOE whatsoever for a new PvP server with capped content aimed at casual players.<br><br>The guild summit illustrated everything that is wrong with EQ. SOE only listens to the minority of players who have no life outside this game. And almost all of the devs are themselves former blue server players who have not the first clue as to what it would take to make a workeable PvP environment. See Lucid Zek if you'd like to know what four programmers (who have a clue about PvP) working in their spare time can do to make a real PvP server.<br><br>For those of you who doubt the audience for a pre-Luclin server, understand this. Most of the audience for such a server ARE NOT ON THESE BOARDS. The are among the 1 million players WHO NO LONGER SUBSCRIBE TO THIS GAME. So as much of an uproar as those of us on this board have been able to create in favor of a pre-Luclin server, it's only a tiny fraction of the people who would actually go buy a new account, as I did, to play on such a world.<br><br>Anyways, I'm done. Enjoy your broken and dying game. I think the main reason why we won't see a PvP Classic Server is because the population of this game has leveled off and is headed into permanent and irrevocable decline. That's why new server launches just don't happen anymore. And SOE wouldn't want to deal with the inevitable whining if they, say, brought down the disastrous failure known as Sullon Zek, or combined Tallon and Vallon.<br><br>So it's your game... enjoy what's left of it.<br><br>Aenor the Betrayer, founder of the Grey Companions, a roleplaying PvP guild in the early days of Vallon Zek before expansion after expansion was launched to meet the PvE demands of EQ lifers.	
		</td></tr>
