		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			<DIV>
<DIV>Bottom line:</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Manufacter classes, gear, levels, aa's&nbsp;to test pVp balance amongst classes.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Goto various zones (indoor, outdoor) and simply pvp as devs.&nbsp; Try variations of discs (consider overpoweredness/underpoweredness &nbsp;of repop timer), try various aa's, spells, etc...see who comes out on top...change zones and try again.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>It should be readily apprent fairly quickly which classes need help, and which do not (need "nerf" help).&nbsp;&nbsp; Reading what biased posters have to say get you nowhere. (how do you know which claim &nbsp;is legit, and which is not if you've nevere tried it ?)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>What do do once you TEST pvp...actuall pvp, not forum responses on how a level 59 XXX class once killed an afk level 64 XXX class.&nbsp;&nbsp; Just like trying to ascertain which car is faster...you could read countless articles about it..OR you could line up both cars with comparable drivers (switch cars if need be), and PROVE which car is inherently faster..&nbsp; Why leave this to chance "opinions" when you could easily get hard data ?</DIV></DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Fix the class discrepencies.&nbsp; Don't buy into the "this class should be all powerful arguement".&nbsp; Fix healing in PvP. (way overpowered comparitively to the DD spells..faster casting, less mana, not hit with th 66% bug means if you can attack AND heal..you are inherently advantaged even over purely offensive classes...this is Backas*words)</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Make it possible to pvp as a caster indoors vs a melee.&nbsp; Make it possible, not so remote you'd have a better chance soloing Quarm then succesfully pvp in an indoor zone vs a EP + melee.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Make resists fairly represented amongst classes.&nbsp; If they have debuffs, they shouldn't have lure resists, if they do not, they should.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>Consider pets into the equation.&nbsp; Pets have and will have far more utility in pvp then they are often given merit for.</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>
<DIV>&nbsp;</DIV>	
		</td></tr>
